@startuml fig-rest-maturity-levels
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12

title Richardson Maturity Model — REST Levels 0 to 3

together {
    card "**Level 0 — The Swamp of POX**\n\nSingle endpoint: POST /api\nAction embedded in body:\n{\"action\": \"get_user\", \"user_id\": 1}\n\nPure RPC tunnelled over HTTP." as L0 #FFCDD2

    card "**Level 1 — Resources**\n\nDistinct URIs: POST /users/1\nAction still in body:\n{\"action\": \"get\"}\n\nResources are addressable\nbut verbs are not used." as L1 #FFE0B2
}

together {
    card "**Level 2 — Verbs + Status Codes**\n\nGET /users/1  → 200\nPOST /users   → 201 + Location\nPUT /users/1  → 200\nDELETE /users/1 → 204\n\nHTTP semantics used correctly." as L2 #BBDEFB

    card "**Level 3 — Hypermedia (HATEOAS)**\n\nResponses include links:\n{\"links\": {\n  \"self\": \"/users/1\",\n  \"update\": \"/users/1\",\n  \"collection\": \"/users\"\n}}\n\nClient discovers actions dynamically." as L3 #C8E6C9
}

L0 -[#1565C0]right-> L1 : introduce\nresources
L1 -[#1565C0]right-> L2 : add HTTP\nverbs
L2 -[#1565C0]right-> L3 : add\nhypermedia

legend bottom
  Level 0 treats HTTP as a transport tunnel.
  Level 2 is the practical standard for most APIs.
  Level 3 enables true decoupling: clients follow
  links rather than hard-coding URL patterns.
endlegend
@enduml
